SIMPLE: picking
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Picking
<hw>Pick"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of digging or
breaking up, as with a pick.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of choosing, plucking, or
gathering.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which is, or may be, picked or
gleaned.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Pilfering; also, that which is pilfered.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>The pulverized shells of oysters
used in making walks.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Simmonds.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>Rough sorting of ore.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>Overburned bricks.</def>
<rj><au>Simmonds.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Picking</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Picking
<hw>Pick"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Done or made as with a
pointed tool; <as>as, a <ex>picking</ex> sound</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Nice; careful.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q> was too warm on <qex>picking</qex> work to dwell.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Picking peg</b></col>. <fld>(Weaving)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Picker</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 3.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pickle</ent>⟦br⟧
